comment: I think this was a very much needed wake up call for the feminist. And I'm saying that as a feminist myself. We simply cannot judge who's the victim or who's not just by relying on information of the public eye. This community needs a more rational approach to such cases. It's not your local domestic violence type of case. It's a public shit show and in that case, the court decides who's at fault and who isn't. We, as a community, have let a victim of abuse down and rooted for his abuser and I hope that this has been a lesson to remember for future cases like that. We cannot yell equality and trust Amber Heard just because she's a woman. That's not how reality works. Johnny Depp deserves a sincere apology but the apology will not repair his image...
